00:30:59.334 --> 00:31:01.049
electron,
it can happen,

00:31:01.049 --> 00:31:04.276
but in those days,
they didn't have a light whose

00:31:04.276 --> 00:31:08.038
intensity was enough to send
enough of these photons.

00:31:08.038 --> 00:31:10.193
But nowadays,
it turns out that if you

00:31:10.193 --> 00:31:13.105
really, really crank up the
intensity, you can make

00:31:13.105 --> 00:31:15.960
electrons come out,
even below the frequency.

00:31:15.960 --> 00:31:19.122
That's because more than one
