01:01:20.989 --> 01:01:23.275
But the question is,
what is the kinematics of

01:01:23.275 --> 01:01:25.918
quantum mechanics compared to
kinematics of classical

01:01:25.918 --> 01:01:26.630
mechanics?
 

01:01:26.630 --> 01:01:29.398
In classical mechanics,
a particle has a definite

01:01:29.398 --> 01:01:31.650
position, it has a definite
momentum.

01:01:31.650 --> 01:01:36.960
That describes the state of the
particle now.

01:01:36.960 --> 01:01:39.405
Then you want to predict the
future, so you want to know the

01:01:39.405 --> 01:01:41.190
